<p>While Bitcoin focuses on being a decentralized digital currency, Ethereum offers a more versatile platform for developing decentralized applications.</p>



<p>The size, growth, and culture of their developer communities also differ.</p>



<p>Ultimately, the innovations driven by developers will shape the adoption and future of Bitcoin and Ethereum.</p>
